About SOAR

What is SOAR?

The Student Organization for Academic Research (SOAR) is an annual conference that brings together undergraduate and graduate students to present their research, engage with academic communities, and build professional networks.

SOAR's History

Since 2015, SOAR has grown from a small gathering of 50 students to a premier research conference hosting over 500 participants annually. We've fostered countless collaborations and launched many successful academic careers.

2015

SOAR founded with 50 participants

2018

Expanded to include graduate students

2022

Reached international participation

2024

Record 500+ participants

Frequently Asked Questions

Who can participate in SOAR?

All undergraduate and graduate students are welcome to attend and present their research.

What research areas are accepted?

We accept research from all disciplines including STEM, humanities, social sciences, and interdisciplinary work.

Is there a registration fee?

Registration fees vary. Early bird rates and student discounts are available.

How do I submit an abstract?

Abstract submissions open in January 2026. Details will be posted on our website and social media.
